---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro'
---
<DocsLayout title="Auto Height Plugin">
  <h1>Auto Height</h1>
  <p class="lead">Animates the slider wrapper height to match the active slide on each navigation. Useful for slides with variable content height.</p>

  <h2>Import</h2>
  <pre><code>import {"{"} autoHeight {"}"} from '@andresclua/sliderkit-plugins'</code></pre>

  <h2>Options</h2>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Option</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>animationDuration</code></td><td><code>number</code></td><td><code>300</code></td><td>Duration in milliseconds for the CSS height transition when the wrapper resizes.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Example</h2>
  <pre><code>{`import { createSlider } from '@andresclua/sliderkit'
import { autoHeight } from '@andresclua/sliderkit-plugins'

createSlider('#my-slider', {
  plugins: [autoHeight({ animationDuration: 400 })],
})`}</code></pre>

  <p>The wrapper height is set via an inline style with a CSS <code>transition</code>. On destroy the inline styles are cleared, restoring default layout behaviour.</p>

  <p><a href="/demos/auto-height">View auto height demo</a></p>
</DocsLayout>
